        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32913",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Please, note that referer might be not present in some cases.\nAdvanced http clients can easilly play with it (spoof it), or simply suppress it",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=doctorrock83",
                        "name": "doctorrock83",
                        "displayName": "julien PAULI",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T13:05:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T13:05:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32928",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rockaut",
                        "name": "rockaut",
                        "displayName": "Markus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes that's true for sure, but like in most cases if you are aware of security concerns it can be usefull.\n\nHmm, maybee if no referer is present it should be false returned or simply null. Don't know witch fits more for ZF.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rockaut",
                        "name": "rockaut",
                        "displayName": "Markus",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-25T12:04:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-25T12:04:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32929",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think it would be better to add a getReferer() method to Zend_Controller_Request_Http which would return null if the referer url could not be determined. Then  you could just feed the url returned by that getReferer() method to the redirector action helper.\n\nBtw, if the referer is always (on lighttpd, apache and IIS) in $_SERVER['HTTP_REFERER'] I think we don't need any of this at all.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-25T12:30:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-25T12:31:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
